
# Merge Time Ranges - NodeJS Module

## Description
This module exports a function mergeTimeRanges that merges overlapping or closely spaced time intervals based on a threshold value.

## Function Signature
js
mergeTimeRanges(ranges, threshold)

- ranges: Array of [start, end] time ranges (in milliseconds)
- threshold: Maximum allowed gap between two ranges to still merge them

##  Example Usage
js
const mergeTimeRanges = require('./my-module.js');

const ranges = [
  [1000, 2000],
  [2500, 4000],
  [3900, 4100],
  [8000, 9000],
  [9050, 9500]
];

const threshold = 200;
console.log(mergeTimeRanges(ranges, threshold));
// Output: [ [1000, 2000], [2500, 4100], [8000, 9500] ]


## File Structure
/merge-time-ranges
- my-module.js     # Main function
- package.json     # Module metadata
- README.md        # How to use the module


## How to Run
1. Place the files in a folder.
2. Run using Node.js:
node test.js

